        "title": "Force java xjc compiler to generate unbounded generics",
        "body": "<p>I have following XSD schema: <\/p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;xs:schema&gt;\n    &lt;xs:complexType name=\"Person\"&gt;\n        &lt;xs:sequence&gt;\n            &lt;xs:element name=\"LastName\"/&gt;\n            &lt;xs:element name=\"FirstName\"/&gt;\n        &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;\n    &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;\n\n    &lt;xs:complexType name=\"ListOfPersons\"&gt;\n        &lt;xs:sequence&gt;\n            &lt;xs:element minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" name=\"Persons\" type=\"Person\"&gt;&lt;/xs:element&gt;\n        &lt;/xs:sequence&gt;\n    &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;\n    &lt;xs:element name=\"List\" type=\"ListOfPersons\"/&gt;\n&lt;/xs:schema&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When i generate java classes with XJC compiler i receive (among others) following class:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class ListOfPersons {\n\n    @XmlElement(name = \"Persons\")\n    protected List&lt;Person&gt; persons;\n\n    public List&lt;Person&gt; getPersons() {\n        if (persons == null) {\n            persons = new ArrayList&lt;Person&gt;();\n        }\n        return this.persons;\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>}<\/p>\n\n<p>My question is. Is there any possibility to generate persons of type <code>List&lt;? extends Person&gt;<\/code> instead of plain <code>List&lt;Person&gt;<\/code>?<\/p>\n",
